#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:2
msgid "Python 2.7 and 3.4 support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:4
msgid ""
"It is demanding on the maintainers of an open source project to support many "
"Python versions, as there's extra cost of keeping code compatible between "
"all versions, while holding back on features only made possible on newer "
"Python versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:8
msgid ""
"In case of Python 2 and 3, the difference between the languages makes it "
"even more prominent, because many new Python 3 features cannot be used in a "
"Python 2/3 compatible code base."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:11
msgid ""
"Python 2.7 EOL has been reached `in 2020 <https://legacy.python.org/dev/peps/"
"pep-0373/#id4>`__, with the last release made in April, 2020."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:14
msgid ""
"Python 3.4 EOL has been reached `in 2019 <https://www.python.org/dev/peps/"
"pep-0429/#release-schedule>`__, with the last release made in March, 2019."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:16
msgid ""
"For those reasons, in Jun 2019 it was decided that **pytest 4.6** series "
"will be the last to support Python 2.7 and 3.4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:19
msgid "What this means for general users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:21
msgid ""
"Thanks to the `python_requires`_ setuptools option, Python 2.7 and Python "
"3.4 users using a modern pip version will install the last pytest 4.6.X "
"version automatically even if 5.0 or later versions are available on PyPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:26
msgid ""
"Users should ensure they are using the latest pip and setuptools versions "
"for this to work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:29
msgid "Maintenance of 4.6.X versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:31
msgid ""
"Until January 2020, the pytest core team ported many bug-fixes from the main "
"release into the ``4.6.x`` branch, with several 4.6.X releases being made "
"along the year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:34
msgid ""
"From now on, the core team will **no longer actively backport patches**, but "
"the ``4.6.x`` branch will continue to exist so the community itself can "
"contribute patches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:37
msgid ""
"The core team will be happy to accept those patches, and make new 4.6.X "
"releases **until mid-2020** (but consider that date as a ballpark, after "
"that date the team might still decide to make new releases for critical "
"bugs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:44
msgid "Technical aspects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:46
msgid ""
"(This section is a transcript from `#5275 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/5275>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:48
msgid ""
"In this section we describe the technical aspects of the Python 2.7 and 3.4 "
"support plan."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:51
msgid "What goes into 4.6.X releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:53
msgid "New 4.6.X releases will contain bug fixes only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:56
msgid "When will 4.6.X releases happen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:58
msgid ""
"New 4.6.X releases will happen after we have a few bugs in place to release, "
"or if a few weeks have passed (say a single bug has been fixed a month after "
"the latest 4.6.X release)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:61
msgid "No hard rules here, just ballpark."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:64
msgid "Who will handle applying bug fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:66
msgid ""
"We core maintainers expect that people still using Python 2.7/3.4 and being "
"affected by bugs to step up and provide patches and/or port bug fixes from "
"the active branches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:69
msgid ""
"We will be happy to guide users interested in doing so, so please don't "
"hesitate to ask."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:71
msgid "**Backporting changes into 4.6**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:73
msgid "Please follow these instructions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:75
msgid "``git fetch --all --prune``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:77
msgid "``git checkout origin/4.6.x -b backport-XXXX`` # use the PR number here"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:79
msgid ""
"Locate the merge commit on the PR, in the *merged* message, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:81
msgid "nicoddemus merged commit 0f8b462 into pytest-dev:features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:83
msgid ""
"``git cherry-pick -m1 REVISION`` # use the revision you found above "
"(``0f8b462``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:85
msgid "Open a PR targeting ``4.6.x``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:87
msgid "Prefix the message with ``[4.6]`` so it is an obvious backport"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:88
msgid "Delete the PR body, it usually contains a duplicate commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:90
msgid "**Providing new PRs to 4.6**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:92
msgid ""
"Fresh pull requests to ``4.6.x`` will be accepted provided that the "
"equivalent code in the active branches does not contain that bug (for "
"example, a bug is specific to Python 2 only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/py27-py34-deprecation.rst:96
msgid ""
"Bug fixes that also happen in the mainstream version should be first fixed "
"there, and then backported as per instructions above."
msgstr ""
